<P>
   911-DISTRESS (Los Angeles) _ If you call 911 on your cellular
telephone in Los Angeles County, there's a 1-in-14 chance you'll
get a busy signal, simply because there are too few operators and
too many callers. By Eric Moses. (Will move in the ``n'' California
and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
</TEXT>
